oots and blood, jaw working as if he chewed old orders into new ones, and beyond all of them the bones of Veloros listen for a pitch that could become a promise.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Present the Arsenal Manifest Page and Saltfang scrapings to the Council at the Vertebrae.\",\n        \"Counter Mara Vell-Seren’s legal argument without slander by citing observed facts.\",\n        \"Decide whether to reveal the existence of the tuning passage behind the dais to neutralize a hostile orator.\",\n        \"Persuade the Council to delay emergency tolls until an inquiry into siphon sabotage concludes.\",\n        \"Deliver a sealed copy of your testimony to the Thalassarium archive.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Tern Quietwake\", \"lines\": \"A city is a throat that must choose its words, and today Thassyl needs a word that buys breath instead of spending it. I ask you to carry into that chamber a clean tone that does not hook to pride, because pride drowns faster than stone. Speak of what your eyes measured and what your fingers found, and let the bones judge weight from that alone. The tuning passage is a temptation with a pious face; it promises fairness while favoring whoever sets the chord, and even a just cause can sour if it leans too hard on hidden gears. If the tide inside you runs fast, breathe twice and match your heart to the low thrum beneath the floor, because bone remembers steadiness and gives it back to those who meet it halfway.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Kael Rimestrand\", \"lines\": \"I will put the page on the lectern and the grit in the bowl, and I will say where I was standing when I learned each thing so no one has to take my word without anchor. I will name the hour that the siphon coughed and the smell of metal that followed, and I will not smear anyone who has not smeared themselves in their own ink. If they try to take my voice by prying at old uniforms or old quarrels, I will let the past be a t